  "texts": [
    "For example, by making appropriate tests easier and inappropriate tests more difficult to select, guidance-and CPOE-based interventions favor efficiency.",
    "In contrast, education, financial incentives, and A&F interventions favor thoroughness.",
    "It also highlights the role of laboratory staff in the pursuit of appropriateness.",
    "As physicians have little time to devote to the proper utilization of laboratory resources, specialists in laboratory medicine should intensify the collaboration to reduce inappropriate testing and to proactively become \"knowledge manager[s]\" [128].",
    "Specialists in laboratory medicine have the responsibility to ensure communication with users in order to provide education on latest evidence for tests selection and advice on appropriate interpretation of tests [129][130][131][132].Inappropriate laboratory testing concerns over-as much as underuse."
